<C>__{jimbo}
<D>__{shoot.}
<L>__{exterior graveyard}
<A>__{a wind gust rocks the casket just as it's lowered into the frozen earth. the funeral breaks up quickly as paul and his wife shake hands with the minister.}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{that was lovely, thank you so much.}
<C>__{minister}
<D>__{margaret, paul, you two get some sleep.}
<A>__{paul looks nervously at margaret, who is about to reply. as her mouth engages, a gust of wind obliterates most of her words, except for...}
<C>__{margaret}
<D>__{...nun banger.}
<A>__{the minister smiles, he must have misunderstood.}
<C>__{minister}
<D>__{absolutely.}
<A>__{paul turns to see ted approaching. a blast of snow obscures his view. when ted reappears, he's just a few steps away.}
<C>__{ted}
<D>__{mr. barnell. there was no hurry on this, we could wait until }
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{it's ok. we just wrapped up. this is my wife, margaret.}
<A>__{as they shake hands, and margaret opens her mouth to speak...}
<C>__{paul }
<D>__{why don't you wait in the car, sweetheart?}
